<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="528" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1201,1802]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1273,1298]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
MALE (
<figureCitation box="[429,528,1273,1298]" captionStart="FIGURES 121 – 131. 121 – 123" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[162,1433,199,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,195,1804]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 121 – 131. 121 – 123. Bakeriella quadriceps, ♀: 121. body, dorsal view; 122. mandible, frontal view; 123. mesopleuron, lateral view. 124 – 126. B. quinquelineata, ♀: 124. body, dorsal view; 125. mandible, frontal view; 126. mesopleuron, lateral view. 127 – 131. B. reclusa, ♂: 127. body, dorsal view; 128. mandible, frontal view; 129. mesopleuron, lateral view; 130. genitalia, ventral view; 131. genitalia, lateral view. Scale bars = 250 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226399/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">
Fig. 
<number box="[485,528,1274,1298]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528" value="127.0">127</number>
</figureCitation>
). Black. Mandible with five apical teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1120,1273,1298]" captionStart="FIGURES 121 – 131. 121 – 123" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[162,1433,199,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,195,1804]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 121 – 131. 121 – 123. Bakeriella quadriceps, ♀: 121. body, dorsal view; 122. mandible, frontal view; 123. mesopleuron, lateral view. 124 – 126. B. quinquelineata, ♀: 124. body, dorsal view; 125. mandible, frontal view; 126. mesopleuron, lateral view. 127 – 131. B. reclusa, ♂: 127. body, dorsal view; 128. mandible, frontal view; 129. mesopleuron, lateral view; 130. genitalia, ventral view; 131. genitalia, lateral view. Scale bars = 250 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226399/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">
Fig. 
<number box="[1074,1120,1274,1298]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528" value="128.0">128</number>
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus with subrounded median lobe. Antennal scrobe wholly carinate. Frons strongly coriaceous. Vertex slightly convex. Pronotal disc with anterior corner angulate; anterior carina thick and straight; lateral carina restricted to anterior fourth, sharp; posterior margin paralleled by series of foveae. Scutellar pit rounded. Mesopleuron with subtegular groove sinuous; anterior fovea subtriangular; upper fovea elliptical; lower fovea with upper margin absent (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1424,1417,1442]" captionStart="FIGURES 121 – 131. 121 – 123" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[162,1433,199,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,195,1804]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 121 – 131. 121 – 123. Bakeriella quadriceps, ♀: 121. body, dorsal view; 122. mandible, frontal view; 123. mesopleuron, lateral view. 124 – 126. B. quinquelineata, ♀: 124. body, dorsal view; 125. mandible, frontal view; 126. mesopleuron, lateral view. 127 – 131. B. reclusa, ♂: 127. body, dorsal view; 128. mandible, frontal view; 129. mesopleuron, lateral view; 130. genitalia, ventral view; 131. genitalia, lateral view. Scale bars = 250 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226399/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">
Fig. 
<number box="[1378,1424,1418,1442]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528" value="129.0">129</number>
</figureCitation>
). Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[270,432,1453,1478]" captionStart="FIGURES 121 – 131. 121 – 123" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[162,1433,199,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,195,1804]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 121 – 131. 121 – 123. Bakeriella quadriceps, ♀: 121. body, dorsal view; 122. mandible, frontal view; 123. mesopleuron, lateral view. 124 – 126. B. quinquelineata, ♀: 124. body, dorsal view; 125. mandible, frontal view; 126. mesopleuron, lateral view. 127 – 131. B. reclusa, ♂: 127. body, dorsal view; 128. mandible, frontal view; 129. mesopleuron, lateral view; 130. genitalia, ventral view; 131. genitalia, lateral view. Scale bars = 250 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226399/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">
Figs 
<number box="[329,432,1454,1478]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528" value="130.131">130, 131</number>
</figureCitation>
): paramere wide, apical margin inclined and almost blunt, basal margin inclined; cuspis divided into two arms, dorsal arm shorter and wider than ventral arm; aedeagus lozenge, ventral surface with conspicuous projection ventrad; base of apodeme very dilated and directed outward.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="528" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1201,1802]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">FEMALE [not examined]. Black. Mandible with five apical teeth. Clypeus with broadly angulate median lobe. Frons strongly coriaceous. Vertex slightly convex. Pronotal disc with anterior corner angulate; posterior margin paralleled by series of foveae. Scutellar pit subrounded.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
