<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="528" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1201,1802]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1705,1730]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">Remarks</emphasis>
. Inner surface of paramere concave, spoon-shaped. I was not able to locate where the single female (allotype) is deposited. It is supposed to be deposited at University of Wisconsin (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1102,1236,1741,1766]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528" refString="Evans, H. E. (1969) A revision of the genus Epyris in the Americas (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 95, 181 - 352." type="journal article" year="1969">
Evans 
<number box="[1176,1236,1741,1766]" pageId="27" pageNumber="528" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but according to Craig 
<collectingCountry box="[220,309,1777,1802]" name="Belgium" pageId="27" pageNumber="528">Brabant</collectingCountry>
(pers. com.) it is not there.
</paragraph>
